mform_migration = MBlock to Repeater
mform_migration_tool = Migration tool
mform_migration_intro = This tool converts MBlock-based module code to the MForm 9 repeater. It only produces suggested code and does not change any modules or stored data.
mform_migration_intro_input = Input: field name prefixes (e.g. "1.0.header") are removed and "MBlock::show(...)" is rewritten to "addRepeaterElement(...)".
mform_migration_intro_output = Output: "rex_var::toArray(\"REX_VALUE[n]\")" is rewritten to "MFormRepeaterHelper::decode(n)" for the repeater slot id.
mform_migration_intro_hint = Review the result before use. Notes below the fields mark constructs that need manual adjustment (e.g. numeric media/link fields).
mform_migration_limitations = Not all modules can be converted fully automatically. Special configurations, external files, or custom logic may require manual adjustments.
mform_migration_module_loaded = Module {0} was loaded.
mform_migration_convert_done = Conversion completed.
mform_migration_batch_dryrun_done = Dry-run completed.
mform_migration_mapping_key1 = Map legacy key "1" to field name
mform_migration_mapping_json = Additional legacy key mapping (JSON)
mform_migration_mapping_note = Optional mapping for old keys, e.g. {"1":"link"} or {"REX_LINK_1":"link"}.
mform_migration_mapping_json_invalid = Legacy key mapping is not a valid JSON object.
mform_migration_repeater_id = Repeater slot id
mform_migration_repeater_id_note = The REX_VALUE slot id of the repeater (matches the MBlock $id, usually 1). Only this slot is rewritten in the output.
mform_migration_input_label = Input code (input.php)
mform_migration_output_label = Output code (output.php)
