mform_migration_data_tool = Data migration (stored content)
mform_migration_data_intro = Converts already stored MBlock data into the flat repeater JSON. Paste the raw value from the slice column (e.g. "value1"). MBlock stores it as {"GBS&lt;hash&gt;":{"VALUE":{"1":[...]}}}, the repeater expects a flat array.
mform_migration_data_label = MBlock raw value (JSON from value column)
mform_migration_data_note = The repeater slot set above is used. The technical field "checkbox_block_hold" is removed, "mblock_offline" becomes "__disabled".
mform_migration_data_convert = Convert data
mform_migration_data_result = Repeater JSON (write back into the same value column)
mform_migration_data_empty = No data converted yet.
mform_migration_data_batch_title = Batch processing for all slices
mform_migration_data_batch_hint = For many slices use a one-off script: read the module slices via rex_sql, pass each value through MBlockToRepeaterConverter::convertData() and write the result back. Always create a DB backup first and test on a staging copy.
mform_migration_batch_tool = Batch migration from database
mform_migration_batch_intro = Reads slices of a module directly from the database, converts the MBlock value in the selected slot column and can write it back on demand. Run a dry-run first, then apply only to selected slices.
