mform_example_description_base = The "basic examples" include the basic calls of the respective MForm element, without any "extras", extensions and validations.
mform_example_description_extended = The "extended examples" show beyond the "basic examples", how to expand elements around attributes, options, parameters, labels, etc.
mform_example_description_expert = The "expert examples" show that MForm can be used for more than just standards.
mform_example_description_community = Later
mform_example_description_wrapper = The "Wrapper Examples" demonstrate how to effectively layout and enhance input forms using MForm wrapper elements.
mform_example_description_repeater = The "Repeater Examples" illustrate how simple it is to use a repeater element. Essentially, it can be created like the other wrapper elements. The wrapped form can be replicated using the repeater as many times as needed, with minimum or maximum block limits (similar to MBlock as before).
mform_example_description_layout_preview = This page demonstrates the two utility classes <code>HtmlToSvgConverter</code> and <code>LayoutPreviewBuilder</code> from the MForm namespace <code>FriendsOfRedaxo\MForm\Utils</code>. <code>LayoutPreviewBuilder</code> programmatically generates SVG layout previews from sections, columns and placeholder elements – ideal as a module preview image in the backend. <code>HtmlToSvgConverter</code> wraps SVG fragments (rect, circle, line, path, text, g, image) into a complete, standalone SVG. The "HTML" part refers to the supported <em>HTML-style attributes</em> (<code>style="background:…; color:…; border: 1px solid red"</code>) on those SVG tags – they are translated to <code>fill</code> / <code>stroke</code> / <code>stroke-width</code>.

